18
00:02:28.890 --> 00:02:30.620
丝绸之路
The Silk Road.


19
00:02:31.860 --> 00:02:35.390
爸爸 我记不起丝绸之路的相关知识了
Baba, I can't remember about the Silk Road.


20
00:02:36.190 --> 00:02:38.990
或许我们可以把这当成一个故事来记
Maybe if we think of it like a story.


21
00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.760
即使我们一无所有 故事也总能记在心间
Stories remain in our hearts even when all else is gone.


22
00:02:42.770 --> 00:02:46.600
自我们的文明伊始 我们的人民就开始讲故事了
Our people have always told stories, from our very beginning,


23
00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:48.840
那时我们的家乡叫作帕提亚和霍拉桑
when we were Parthia and Khorasan.


24
00:02:51.740 --> 00:02:55.510
我们的家园在兴都库什山脉的利爪下被分成数个部分
A fractured land in the claws of the Hindu Kush mountains,


25
00:02:55.510 --> 00:02:59.710
有北部沙漠那炽烈之眼的灼热
scorched by the fiery eyes of the Northern Deserts,


26
00:02:59.720 --> 00:03:02.750
亦包括那黑白交汇的冰峰之凛冽
black rubble earth against ice peaks.


27
00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:06.790
我们的家园就如一个凶兽的骨架
Our land was the petrified skeleton of a monster.


28
00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:09.520
我们的家园叫阿里亚纳
We were Ariana,


29
00:03:09.530 --> 00:03:12.000
是高尚与荣耀之乡
the land of the noble and honorable.


30
00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:16.200
我们可谓是世界交通的枢纽
We were a pathway to everywhere,


31
00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:18.870
让东西方可互通有无
carrying goods from east to west.


32
00:03:20.070 --> 00:03:21.740
我们研究星象
We studied the stars


33
00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:24.940
在混乱的星空中寻找规律
and began to see order amidst the chaos.


34
00:03:24.940 --> 00:03:29.010
我们的人民中涌现许多科学家 哲学家和故事传唱人
We were scientists, philosophers, and storytellers.


35
00:03:29.010 --> 00:03:32.680
为解答疑惑而探求真知
Questions sought answers and then more questions.


36
00:03:32.680 --> 00:03:36.180
我们开始了解宇宙中我们的位置
We began to see our place in the universe.


37
00:03:36.190 --> 00:03:39.890
但我们处于两个交战国的边境交汇处
But we were at the edges of empires at war with each other,


38
00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:42.720
数千年以来
as borders were defined and redefined...


39
00:03:42.730 --> 00:03:45.700
边境无数次被重新界定
over thousands of years.


40
00:03:46.930 --> 00:03:50.800
无数统治者在此开战 有波斯的居鲁士二世大帝
Of these mighty rulers came Cyrus the Great of Persia.


41
00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:55.610
还有马其顿王国的亚历山大大帝
Then Alexander the Great of Macedon.


42
00:03:56.240 --> 00:03:58.940
有印度的孔雀王朝
There came the Mauryan Empire,


43
00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:00.880
也有成吉思汗的铁骑
Genghis Khan,


44
00:04:00.880 --> 00:04:03.250
还有好多好多
and so on and so on.


45
00:04:03.250 --> 00:04:05.810
每次战争都血流成河
Each time there was bloodshed,


46
00:04:05.820 --> 00:04:08.020
而每次战争也都会有幸存者
and each time there were survivors.


47
00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:11.620
历史的轨迹不断地重复着
A pattern repeating itself endlessly.


48
00:04:15.190 --> 00:04:16.960
帕尔瓦娜 我年轻的时候
When I was young, Parvana,


49
00:04:16.960 --> 00:04:20.960
在这个城市里 我体验过和平的滋味
I knew what peace felt like, here in this city.


50
00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:25.130
孩子们都会去读书 女人们也能上大学
Children went to school, women went to university.


51
00:04:25.140 --> 00:04:27.940
这里成了世外桃源
All the empires forgot about us,


52
00:04:27.940 --> 00:04:29.140
至少有那么一段时间是
for a while at least.


53
00:04:30.740 --> 00:04:32.740
但好景不长
But it did not last.


54
00:04:32.740 --> 00:04:35.610
我们的国土变得脆弱不堪
The ground became weak under our feet,


55
00:04:35.610 --> 00:04:37.950
从未安定
always uncertain.


56
00:04:37.950 --> 00:04:41.180
先是一场政变 又来了一次入侵
First came a coup d'état, then an invasion,


57
00:04:41.180 --> 00:04:42.890
之后就是内战
then a civil war.


58
00:04:44.050 --> 00:04:45.620
如此的混乱局面下
In the chaos,


59
00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:48.760
有些人希望领袖可以恢复秩序
some looked to those who might restore order.


60
00:04:50.130 --> 00:04:51.790
但那代价实在是太大了
But at a great cost.


61
00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:55.160
我们给女性定下了严格的德行规范
We have determined specific dignity for women!


62
00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:59.270
女人决不能外出 招惹不必要的关注
Women should not go outside and attract unnecessary attention!


63
00:04:59.270 --> 00:05:03.800
如果女人向外人展露自己的容貌 她将受到伊斯兰教法的诅咒
If a woman shows herself, she will be cursed by the Islamic Sharia


64
00:05:03.810 --> 00:05:06.210
永远也别想上天堂
and should never expect to go to heaven.


65
00:05:06.210 --> 00:05:08.780
一切都变了 帕尔瓦娜
Everything changes, Parvana.


66
00:05:08.780 --> 00:05:10.880
记录这些的故事提醒着我们
Stories remind us of that.


67
00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:17.920
帕尔瓦娜 你到底有没有在听啊？
Parvana, were you listening at all?


68
00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:19.190
我在听呢 爸爸
Yes, Baba.


69
00:05:19.190 --> 00:05:23.060
要不你给我讲讲我们游牧民族的祖先
Why don't you tell me about our nomadic ancestors


70
00:05:23.060 --> 00:05:25.600
和他们那些金山的事 好不好？
and their hills of gold?


71
00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:27.960
好吧
Well?


72
00:05:27.960 --> 00:05:29.730
2000年前

73
00:05:30.670 --> 00:05:33.800
- 然后呢？ - 2000年前...
- Yes? - 2,000 years ago...


74
00:05:34.840 --> 00:05:37.940
有一位巴克特里亚王国公主
there was a Bactrian princess


75
00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:40.380
她有一个王冠
who had a crown.


76
00:05:40.380 --> 00:05:42.340
然后呢？
And?


77
00:05:42.350 --> 00:05:44.210
- 然后...- 帕尔瓦娜？
- And... - Parvana?


78
00:05:44.210 --> 00:05:46.680
走开 别碰我的东西
Away. Keep away from my things.


79
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:49.950
快走 我说快走 你这只蠢狗
Go away. I said go away, you silly dog!


80
00:05:49.950 --> 00:05:52.890
嘿 你 你以为你在干什么？
Hey, you! What do you think you're doing?


81
00:05:52.890 --> 00:05:54.150
这个女孩为什么乱喊？
Why is this girl shouting?


82
00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:56.390
她只是个孩子 她无意引人注目
She is only a child. She meant nothing by it.


83
00:05:56.390 --> 00:05:58.160
她就是在引人注意
She's drawing attention to herself!


84
00:05:58.160 --> 00:06:00.730
她应该待在家里 而不是在市场抛头露面
She should be at home, not displaying herself in the market.


85
00:06:00.730 --> 00:06:04.070
我家除了一个婴儿 没有男孩 我需要她帮我
I have no son at home, except an infant. I need my daughter to help me.


86
00:06:04.070 --> 00:06:05.730
- 站起来 我们跟你说话呢 - 我是个残..
- Stand up when we talk to you. - I am a cr...


87
00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:07.040
我说给我站起来
I said stand up!


88
00:06:13.780 --> 00:06:15.910
- 我认得你 - 是的 伊德瑞斯
- I know you. - Yes, Idrees.


89
00:06:15.910 --> 00:06:18.150
我以前给你上过课 你那时是个好学生
I was your teacher once. You were a good student.


90
00:06:18.150 --> 00:06:21.050
你给我讲那堆没用的东西 浪费了我宝贵的时间
You wasted my time, teaching me things of no worth.


91
00:06:21.050 --> 00:06:24.690
我已加入塔利班 现在是专杀伊斯兰敌人的战士
I have joined the Taliban and now I fight the enemies of Islam.


92
00:06:24.690 --> 00:06:29.260
好吧 如果我也能算是敌人 那真主已经夺走了我的腿来惩罚我的罪
Well, if I am an enemy, then for my sins God has taken my leg.


93
00:06:29.260 --> 00:06:31.130
老头 你敢嘲笑我？
Are you making fun of me, old man?


94
00:06:31.130 --> 00:06:34.760
我在战争中失去了一条腿 那场我们并肩作战的战争
I lost my leg in the war. The war we fought together.


95
00:06:34.770 --> 00:06:36.930
- 她多大了？- 伊德瑞斯
- How old is the girl? - Idrees.


96
00:06:36.930 --> 00:06:38.900
- 她还是个孩子 - 她这岁数已经能嫁人了
- She is a child. - She's old enough to marry.


97
00:06:38.900 --> 00:06:40.730
我也快要讨老婆了
I'll be looking for a wife soon.


98
00:06:40.740 --> 00:06:42.740
她已经许配给别人了
She's already been promised to someone.


99
00:06:42.740 --> 00:06:44.440
她得把自己裹好
Well, she should cover herself properly.


100
00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:46.840
- 或许你该把眼睛从她身上拿开 - 你跟我说什么？
- Maybe you should stop looking at her. - What did you say to me?


101
00:06:46.840 --> 00:06:49.010
我说你把你那双眼睛拿开
I said stop looking at her.


102
00:06:49.010 --> 00:06:50.880
- 我杀了你 - 伊德瑞斯
- I can have you killed! - Idrees.


103
00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:53.080
- 注意你的言辞 - 够了 走吧
- You watch what you say! - That's enough. Come on.


104
00:06:55.790 --> 00:06:57.420
你还好吗？
Are you all right?


105
00:06:57.420 --> 00:06:59.250
我没事 爸爸
Yes, Baba.


106
00:06:59.260 --> 00:07:00.790
不愧是我的好女儿
That's my girl.


107
00:07:01.290 --> 00:07:02.890
我们回家吧
Let's go home now.


108
00:07:18.380 --> 00:07:20.010
帕尔瓦娜？
Parvana?


109
00:07:21.180 --> 00:07:24.280
你跟那男的说我已经许配给别人了
You told that boy I was promised to someone.


110
00:07:24.280 --> 00:07:26.110
我是要结婚了吗？
Am I getting married?


111
00:07:26.120 --> 00:07:28.920
当然不是 你还是个孩子呢
Of course not. You are still a child.


112
00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:31.320
我现在只想让你天天玩耍 讲讲故事就好
I want you playing and telling stories.


113
00:07:31.320 --> 00:07:33.190
我长大了 不愿意讲什么故事了
I'm too old for that now.


114
00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:36.290
长大了就不爱故事了？ 你一直很爱故事啊
Too old for stories? You've always loved stories.


115
00:07:36.290 --> 00:07:38.230
讲故事能有什么用？
What's the use?


116
00:07:50.210 --> 00:07:53.040
我跟你妈妈谈几句 一切都会好起来的
I'll have a word with Mama-jan and we'll sort it all out.


117
00:07:53.040 --> 00:07:54.780
求你别提那裙子的事
Please don't mention the dress.


118
00:08:00.050 --> 00:08:02.950
要不她会唠叨个没完的
Then I'll never hear the end of it.


119
00:08:02.950 --> 00:08:05.290
- 什么没完？ - 没事 妈妈
- The end of what? - Nothing, Mama-jan.


120
00:08:05.290 --> 00:08:07.920
我们不卖帕尔瓦娜的漂亮裙子了
We're not selling Parvana's good dress.


121
00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:10.420
爸爸 我说的不是这个
Baba, that's not what I meant.


122
00:08:10.430 --> 00:08:12.490
我们需要钱 孩子她爸
We need the money, Baba.


123
00:08:12.500 --> 00:08:16.300
这几天市场比较萧条 过一阵就好了
We'll hold off for a bit. I think business will pick up.


124
00:08:16.300 --> 00:08:19.370
如果经济好起来 我们当然不用卖这裙子
If business picks up, then we won't have to sell it, sure.


125
00:08:19.370 --> 00:08:23.170
但是理想很遥远 现实很骨感 我们必须卖掉它
But the sky is far and the earth is hard. We will have to sell it soon.


126
00:08:24.200 --> 00:08:25.240
好吧 那饭前讲个故事如何？
Well, what about a little story before dinner?


127
00:08:25.240 --> 00:08:28.840
这样暂时我们都不会因裙子的事而烦心了
And we'll forget all about dresses for a while.


128
00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:31.410
或许帕尔瓦娜想给我们讲个故事？
Maybe Parvana would like to read something for us?


129
00:08:31.410 --> 00:08:34.120
现在我不想讲 妈妈 我好累
Not right now, Mama-jan. I'm tired.


130
00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:36.990
她跟我说她已经长大了
She's not a child anymore, she tells me.


131
00:08:36.990 --> 00:08:39.250
所以她现在不喜欢故事了
So she doesn't like stories.


132
00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:42.860
别急着当大人 宝贝女儿
Don't be in such a hurry to grow up, my sweet girl.


133
00:08:42.860 --> 00:08:45.230
长大并没你想的那么好
It might not be all that you expect.


134
00:08:45.230 --> 00:08:48.500
我们家没水了 今早你带回来的水不够
We're out of water. You didn't bring enough this morning.


135
00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:50.430
门边不是有半桶水嘛
But there's half a bucket by the door.


136
00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:54.540
我在你这岁数的时候 家里从来没缺过水
When I was young enough to fetch water, the buckets were never empty.


137
00:08:54.540 --> 00:08:56.400
- 嘿 - 你们俩别闹了
- Hey! - Girls, stop it.


138
00:08:56.410 --> 00:08:59.470
如果你不去井里打水的话
Either you go out and get more water after dinner...


139
00:08:59.480 --> 00:09:01.980
你就得给扎西换尿布
or you can wash Zaki's dirty diapers.


140
00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:04.510
你今天怎么样？ - 好多了
- How are you feeling? - Better.


141
00:09:04.510 --> 00:09:05.980
有你在我就好多了
Now that you're here.


142
00:09:05.980 --> 00:09:11.120
要不是你总洗头 也许水不会这么快就用光呢
Maybe if you didn't wash your hair so much, we wouldn't run out so quickly.


143
00:09:11.120 --> 00:09:14.050
- 帕尔瓦娜 - 要尊重你姐姐
- Parvana. - You should have some respect.


144
00:09:14.060 --> 00:09:16.860
你们怎么不吃呢？
Why don't you eat, hmm?


145
00:09:16.860 --> 00:09:21.100
- 吃饱了一切才会好起来 - 好的
- Things always look better when your belly is full. - Yes, Maudar.


146
00:09:32.040 --> 00:09:34.440
扎西 扎西 等我先把你袖子卷好
Zaki, Zaki, wait till I pull up your sleeves.


147
00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:36.040
不要嘛 妈妈
No, Mama-jan.


148
00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:39.050
这样就好啦
There. There you go.


149
00:09:39.050 --> 00:09:43.180
别把葡萄干都吃了 帕尔瓦娜 那是留给扎西的
Don't eat all the raisins, Parvana. Leave them for Zaki.


150
00:09:43.190 --> 00:09:46.520
你怎么不把你下巴上的那粒大葡萄干给扎西呢 苏拉娅？
Why don't you give him that big raisin on your chin, Soraya?


151
00:09:46.520 --> 00:09:48.890
哦 不对 那不是葡萄干
Oh, but it's not a raisin.


152
00:09:48.890 --> 00:09:50.990
是个长毛的大痣
It's a big, hairy mole.


153
00:09:51.860 --> 00:09:54.400
帕尔瓦娜 向苏拉娅道歉
Parvana, apologize to Soraya.


154
00:09:58.200 --> 00:09:59.840
帕尔瓦娜？
Parvana?


155
00:10:05.940 --> 00:10:08.210
他就在里面 我看他进去的
He's in there! I saw him!


156
00:10:08.210 --> 00:10:09.980
- 如果家里有女人... - 爸爸？
- If there are women present... - Baba?


157
00:10:09.980 --> 00:10:11.850
把自己裹好
Cover yourselves now!


158
00:10:13.950 --> 00:10:16.180
就这个人 他是伊斯兰的敌人
That's the man. An enemy of Islam.


159
00:10:16.190 --> 00:10:19.450
他有禁书 还教女人读禁书
He's got forbidden books, and he's teaching the women with them!


160
00:10:19.460 --> 00:10:21.360
- 放过我们吧 - 他什么也没干
- Leave us be! - He's done nothing!


161
00:10:21.360 --> 00:10:26.260
拿孺拉·阿利在 跟我们走一趟吧
Nurullah Alizai, you must come with us.


162
00:10:26.260 --> 00:10:27.630
爸爸
Baba!


163
00:10:27.630 --> 00:10:30.200
- 你们不能带他走 - 爸爸
- You can't take him! - Baba!


164
00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:32.330
爸爸
Baba-jan!


165
00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:36.270
你们要带他去哪？
Where is he being taken?


166
00:10:36.270 --> 00:10:38.270
去监狱
To prison.


167
00:10:38.280 --> 00:10:41.180
普利查西监狱的人会好好教育他的
They'll teach him a good lesson in Pul-e-Charkhi.


168
00:10:42.240 --> 00:10:44.280
爸爸
Baba!


169
00:10:44.280 --> 00:10:45.950
爸爸
Baba!


170
00:11:07.570 --> 00:11:11.540
妈妈？ 我能开灯吗？
Mama-jan? Can I light the lamp?


171
00:11:11.540 --> 00:11:14.980
嘘 帕尔瓦娜 你会吵醒扎西的
Hush, Parvana. You'll wake Zaki.


172
00:11:14.980 --> 00:11:16.940
可如果他们放过了爸爸
But if they let Baba go,


173
00:11:16.950 --> 00:11:19.710
他需要灯光才能看到家在哪
he'll need a light in the window to see home.


174
00:11:19.720 --> 00:11:23.250
他怎么可能还回得来？他连他的拐杖都没来得及带走
How could he come home? He doesn't even have his stick to walk with.


175
00:11:25.690 --> 00:11:28.420
快睡觉吧 都会好起来的
Go back to sleep. It will be all right.


176
00:11:28.430 --> 00:11:31.430
你怎么知道的 妈妈？你怎么知道？
How do you know that, Mama-jan? How do you know?


177
00:11:31.430 --> 00:11:35.100
别说了 帕尔瓦娜 妈妈已经够愁的了
Be quiet, Parvana. She has enough to worry about.


178
00:11:46.510 --> 00:11:48.440
嘿 扎西 别拽了
Hey! Zaki, stop it.


179
00:11:50.050 --> 00:11:52.050
起床了 帕尔瓦娜 别闹了
Get up, Parvana. Stop playing around.


180
00:11:52.050 --> 00:11:53.610
为什么？怎么回事？
Why? What's going on?


181
00:11:53.620 --> 00:11:55.280
你跟我去找你爸爸
You and I are going to find Baba.


182
00:11:55.290 --> 00:11:59.190
那个男孩说你爸爸在普利查西监狱 我们今天就去那
The boy said he was being taken to Pul-e-Charkhi prison, so that's where we are going.


183
00:11:59.190 --> 00:12:01.090
但是没有爸爸 我们不能出门
But we can't go outside without Baba.


184
00:12:01.090 --> 00:12:03.190
苏拉娅正在写一封给监狱长的信
Soraya is writing a letter for the prison governor


185
00:12:03.190 --> 00:12:05.560
信中对拿孺拉被捕事件提出抗议并请求立即释放你爸爸
to protest Nurullah's arrest and ask for his release.


186
00:12:05.560 --> 00:12:08.530
至少我能把信给他们 - 妈妈 这是不允许的
- At least I can give them that. - Mama-jan, it's not allowed.


187
00:12:08.530 --> 00:12:11.730
如果不引人注意的话 我们不会有问题的
We might be all right if we don't draw attention to ourselves.


188
00:12:11.730 --> 00:12:13.530
- 但我们不能... - 行了 帕尔瓦娜
- But we can't... - Come on, Parvana.


189
00:12:13.540 --> 00:12:16.340
带上你爸爸的拐杖 准备出发
And bring Baba's walking stick. We have to get going.


190
00:12:26.350 --> 00:12:28.080
妈妈
Mama.


191
00:12:48.440 --> 00:12:50.300
嘿
Hey.


192
00:12:50.310 --> 00:12:52.240
嘿 你
Hey, you!


193
00:12:54.610 --> 00:12:57.410
问安 你能告诉我普利查西监狱是哪个方向吗？
Salaam. Can you tell me the way to Pul-e-Charkhi?


194
00:12:57.410 --> 00:13:01.720
问安 过河后向东走
Salaam. Uh, it's east, past the river.


195
00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:04.220
- 但是路很远 - 谢谢您
- But it's a long way. - Thank you, sir.


196
00:13:04.220 --> 00:13:07.460
听好 你们得从老城穿过去 要不你们会被抓的
Listen. Go through the old town, or you'll be caught.


197
00:13:28.550 --> 00:13:31.250
为什么你们独自在外？
Why are you out here by yourself?


198
00:13:31.250 --> 00:13:33.180
- 你丈夫呢？ - 我没办法啊
- Where is your husband? - I have no choice.


199
00:13:33.180 --> 00:13:36.120
没有成年男性伴随 女人禁止独自出门
It's not permitted to be out here without your husband or your brother.


200
00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:38.150
- 对不起 我知道的 - 你懂吗？
- I'm sorry. I know. - Do you understand?


201
00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:41.220
我带着这封抗议我丈夫的抓捕行为的信...- 别废话 快回家
- I am bringing a letter protesting my husband's arrest... - Just go home.


202
00:13:41.220 --> 00:13:42.720
- 不行 - “不行”是什么意思？
- No! - What do you mean, "no"?


203
00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:44.460
这是我的丈夫 拿孺拉·阿利在
This is Nurullah Alizai, my husband.


204
00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:47.160
- 他在无指控前提下昨晚被捕 - 禁止留照片
- He was arrested last night with no charges laid against him. - Photographs are forbidden!


205
00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:50.600
- 我家里只剩女人了... - 你想干什么？ 又是给我看照片...
- I have no one at home... - What are you doing, showing me a photograph?


206
00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:54.100
- 又是在外抛头露面的 快滚回家 - 我家里只有女人和孩子
- Out here by yourself. Go home! - There is no one in my house except for children.


207
00:13:54.100 --> 00:13:58.510
你不能在外面闲逛 你懂吗？立即回家
You have no business out here. Do you understand? Go home. Immediately.


208
00:13:59.740 --> 00:14:01.610
你这是自找麻烦
You're looking for trouble now!


209
00:14:10.690 --> 00:14:13.320
你是你丈夫和民族的耻辱
You are an insult to your husband, to your race!


210
00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:15.460
我得知道他现在状况如何
I need to find out what happened to him!


211
00:14:15.460 --> 00:14:19.130
闭嘴
Shut up!


212
00:14:33.510 --> 00:14:36.510
去监狱也没什么用
Going to the prison will change nothing.


213
00:14:36.510 --> 00:14:39.310
如果你去监狱惹麻烦
If you make trouble like this,


214
00:14:39.320 --> 00:14:43.180
你丈夫会因你的无礼行为而受重罚的
your husband will be punished severely for your insolence.


215
00:14:43.190 --> 00:14:47.120
如果你再看到你在外不回家的话 我会把你抓起来的
And if I find you out here again by yourself, I will arrest you.


216
00:14:47.820 --> 00:14:49.360
现在回家
Now go.


217
00:14:55.530 --> 00:14:57.400
妈妈？
Mama-jan?


218
00:14:57.400 --> 00:14:59.370
带我回家
Take me home.


219
00:16:05.800 --> 00:16:07.500
- 还要 - 嘘
- More! - Shh.


220
00:16:07.500 --> 00:16:10.300
去打水 帕尔瓦娜 家里没水了
Go get water, Parvana. We have none left.


221
00:16:10.310 --> 00:16:12.680
快去
Come on.


222
00:16:41.970 --> 00:16:44.270
滚出去
Get out!


223
00:16:45.410 --> 00:16:47.610
你想干什么？
What are you up to?


224
00:16:48.610 --> 00:16:50.610
快离开这 他们会看到你的
Get out of here. They'll see you!


225
00:16:51.510 --> 00:16:53.310
嘿 站住
Hey, stop!


226
00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:55.690
听见没 我让你站住
Stop when I tell you!


227
00:17:00.790 --> 00:17:02.590
来这边
Through here!


228
00:17:04.060 --> 00:17:06.330
站住
Stop!


229
00:17:06.330 --> 00:17:07.930
那男孩往哪跑了？
Where did that boy go?


230
00:17:07.930 --> 00:17:09.630
你看到了吗？看到他了吗？
Did you see? Did you see?


231
00:17:11.530 --> 00:17:13.500
- 嘿 那个女孩你别跑 - 嘿
- Hey, you! Girl! - Hey!


232
00:17:13.500 --> 00:17:15.640
- 别跑 - 别管那个女孩了
- Come on! - Forget about her!


233
00:17:20.340 --> 00:17:23.010
帕尔瓦娜 你只打回来半桶水
Parvana, this is only half a bucket.


234
00:17:23.010 --> 00:17:24.880
你不能打满一桶水再回来吗？
Couldn't you fill them up all the way?


235
00:17:24.880 --> 00:17:28.550
扎西 嘘 别吵醒妈妈
Zaki, shh. Don't wake her.


236
00:17:28.550 --> 00:17:31.850
- 嘘 扎西 - 妈妈
- Hush, Zaki. - Mama-jan!


237
00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:33.790
- 嘘 - 哄他安静下来 帕尔瓦娜
- Shh. - Sooth him, Parvana.


238
00:17:33.790 --> 00:17:35.460
妈妈
Mama-jan.


239
00:17:35.460 --> 00:17:36.990
给他讲个故事
Tell him a story.


240
00:17:36.990 --> 00:17:38.630
妈妈...
Mama...


241
00:17:38.630 --> 00:17:41.360
很久很久以前
One time in the distant past,


242
00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:44.960
在兴都库什山脚下有个小村庄
there was a little village at the foot of the Hindu Kush mountains.


243
00:17:44.970 --> 00:17:47.870
- 我想要妈妈 - 嘘 好好听故事
- I want Mama-jan. - Shh. Listen.


244
00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:52.340
村民刚得到许多珍贵的种子
The villagers had just managed to gather precious seeds.


245
00:17:52.340 --> 00:17:56.740
为此 他们载歌载舞 开怀大吃
And so, there was dancing and singing and laughing and eating.


246
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:58.950
每个人都洋溢着欢乐的笑容
Everyone was happy.


247
00:17:58.950 --> 00:18:00.950
尤其是一个男孩
Especially for one boy


248
00:18:00.950 --> 00:18:04.980
歌 舞 笑 吃 属他最欢
who danced and sang and laughed and ate more than anyone else.


249
00:18:20.140 --> 00:18:24.770
正当村民载歌载舞 开怀大吃的时候
While the villagers were dancing and singing and laughing and eating,


250
00:18:24.770 --> 00:18:25.910
怪物来袭了
monsters were coming.


251
00:18:33.520 --> 00:18:36.690
怪物们吓跑了驴子 啃食了树木
The monsters frightened the donkeys and ate the trees.


252
00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:43.920
他们偷走了全村最宝贵的东西...
They stole the most precious thing in the whole village...


253
00:18:45.560 --> 00:18:47.400
明年用来耕种的种子
the seeds for next year's crop.


254
00:18:50.870 --> 00:18:54.670
然后怪物们跑回其主人栖息的兴都库什山脉...
Then they ran back to the Hindu Kush mountains where their master lay...


255
00:18:54.670 --> 00:18:58.540
它就是可怕的象王 有着像尖刺一样的象牙
the dreadful Elephant King with spikes for tusks.


256
00:18:58.540 --> 00:19:01.910
嗷儿！
Grrrroar!


257
00:19:01.910 --> 00:19:05.580
嗷儿！嗷儿！
Grroar! Grroar!


258
00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:07.880
嗷儿！
Grroar!


259
00:19:09.750 --> 00:19:11.390
妈妈
Mama-jan.


260
00:19:39.920 --> 00:19:44.520
求你快吃吧 妈妈 吃饱了才会好受些
Please eat, Mama-jan. You'll feel better when your belly is full.


261
00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:06.470
我们家快断粮了
There's hardly any food left.


262
00:20:06.480 --> 00:20:08.680
那我去集市
I'll go to the market.


263
00:20:19.820 --> 00:20:22.490
- 问安  - 问安  请给我12个橙子
- Salaam. - Salaam. Twelve oranges, please.


264
00:20:23.090 --> 00:20:24.690
100阿富汗尼

265
00:20:25.860 --> 00:20:27.430
谢谢
Thank you.


266
00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:33.270
问安 请问6个苹果要多少钱？
Salaam. How much for six apples, please?


267
00:20:33.270 --> 00:20:35.670
问安 孩子 我不能卖给你
Salaam, child. I can't serve you.


268
00:20:35.670 --> 00:20:38.000
但是 先生 求你了 能卖给我6个苹果吗？
But, sir, can I please have six apples?


269
00:20:38.010 --> 00:20:41.770
- 让你的爸爸来买吧   - 我爸爸被带走了
- Get your father to buy food for you. - My father has been taken.


270
00:20:41.780 --> 00:20:43.980
对不起 要不你晚点再来买吧
I'm sorry. Maybe come back later.


271
00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:09.840
就那样被偷了 但是你懂的...
Literally stolen. But you know...


272
00:21:09.840 --> 00:21:13.510
问安 我能买1公斤米吗？
Salaam. Can I have a kilo of rice, please?


273
00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:17.210
- 问安  - 嘿 说你呢
- Salaam. - Hey, you!


274
00:21:17.210 --> 00:21:19.080
女孩
Girl!


275
00:21:19.080 --> 00:21:20.520
嘿 站住
Hey, stop!


276
00:21:23.590 --> 00:21:25.060
我让你站住你就站住
Stop when I tell you!


277
00:21:33.300 --> 00:21:35.500
回去 回家去
Go! Go home!


278
00:21:38.300 --> 00:21:39.830
我把包弄丢了
I dropped the bag.


279
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.600
- 嘘  - 我把钱给丢了
- Hush. - I lost the money.


280
00:21:41.600 --> 00:21:43.800
- 头往后仰着  - 但是我还是可以去挑水的
- Keep your head back. - I can get the water though.


281
00:21:43.810 --> 00:21:45.880
现在先别担心这些
Don't worry about that now.


282
00:21:46.780 --> 00:21:48.910
我给你留了一块馕饼
I saved you a piece of naan.


283
00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:52.550
我给你热一下 就会又好吃又新鲜 好不好？
I'll heat it up for you so it's nice and fresh. All right?


284
00:22:13.800 --> 00:22:16.800
- 我们该怎么办？ - 我也不知道
- What are we going to do? - I don't know.


285
00:22:16.810 --> 00:22:20.040
也许明早我早点出去 在市场人多起来之前买吃的回来
Maybe if I go out early, before it's crowded.


286
00:22:20.040 --> 00:22:21.810
没用的 帕尔瓦娜
It won't work, Parvana.


287
00:22:21.810 --> 00:22:25.350
市场里的人不会冒险东西卖给你的
Market sellers won't risk getting in trouble for serving you.


288
00:22:25.350 --> 00:22:27.950
妈妈的表兄住在马扎里沙里夫
Mama-jan has cousins in Mazar-e-Sharif.


289
00:22:27.950 --> 00:22:30.050
我可以写信请他们帮帮忙
I could write to them for help.


290
00:22:30.050 --> 00:22:34.620
但是我们跟他们连面都没见过 你怎么知道他们会帮忙呢？
But we've never even met them. How do you know they will help?


291
00:22:34.620 --> 00:22:36.090
我们现在就需要食物啊
We need food now.


292
00:24:21.900 --> 00:24:23.830
这些是你哥哥的旧衣服
These were your brother's clothes.


293
00:24:23.830 --> 00:24:27.040
它们很大 但是穿的时候向上提一提就好
They will be big, but we can take them up a bit.


294
00:24:28.440 --> 00:24:31.270
我看起来像男孩吗？
Do I look like a boy?


295
00:24:31.270 --> 00:24:34.010
你看起来像苏莱曼
You look like Sulayman.


296
00:24:34.010 --> 00:24:36.210
- 太像了 - 妈妈
- So much like him. - Mama-jan.


297
00:24:36.210 --> 00:24:38.810
他是个好男孩
He was such a good boy.


298
00:24:38.810 --> 00:24:42.080
他那会儿也不比你现在大多少
Not much older than you are now.


299
00:24:42.080 --> 00:24:43.190
嘘
Shh.


300
00:24:44.420 --> 00:24:46.420
没事的 妈妈
It's all right, Mama-jan.


301
00:24:46.420 --> 00:24:49.960
帕尔瓦娜要去集市买食物 还要打水
Parvana is going to the market for food and water.


302
00:24:49.960 --> 00:24:52.960
只有这个办法了 妈妈 我们什么都没有了
It's the only way, Mama-Jan. We have nothing left.


303
00:25:13.280 --> 00:25:16.520
但是这些果汁是温的 我才不要温的果汁
But these juices are warm. I don't want warm juice.


304
00:25:43.010 --> 00:25:46.110
是的 我就是那么说的 但是你知道的...
Yes, that's what I said, but you know...


305
00:25:46.120 --> 00:25:48.410
问安 向您问安
Salaam. Salaam!


306
00:25:48.420 --> 00:25:50.220
打扰下 问安
Excuse me. Salaam!


307
00:25:50.220 --> 00:25:52.950
问安 问安  进来吧 小伙子
Salaam! Salaam! Come inside, boy!


308
00:25:52.960 --> 00:25:56.130
我又不送货 是吧！
I'm not going to deliver, am I?


309
00:25:58.290 --> 00:26:01.100
就是这么回事 你知道了吧？
But you know how it goes, right?


310
00:26:03.300 --> 00:26:05.370
说吧 你要买什么
Well, let's hear it.


311
00:26:05.370 --> 00:26:10.240
我要买一公斤大米 半公斤小扁豆 和一小点葡萄干
I need a kilo of rice, a half kilo of lentils, and a small amount of raisins.


312
00:26:11.470 --> 00:26:13.110
一小点
A small amount?


313
00:26:13.110 --> 00:26:15.470
卖你多少按我的想象来？
Should I go by my imagination?


314
00:26:15.480 --> 00:26:17.180
是的
Yes.


315
00:26:17.180 --> 00:26:20.110
这孩子 不是很灵光啊
Not very bright, this one.


316
00:26:20.120 --> 00:26:24.450
烂铁也造不出利剑啊
Poor iron won't make a sharp sword.


317
00:26:24.450 --> 00:26:27.020
看看他的傻笑
Look at him smiling!


318
00:26:27.020 --> 00:26:30.520
这孩子都不知道我们在取笑他什么
Little guy doesn't even know when he's being made fun of.


319
00:26:30.530 --> 00:26:33.060
谢谢您 非常感谢
Thank you. Thank you very, very much.


320
00:26:54.120 --> 00:26:56.220
茶都洒出来了
You're spilling the tea.


321
00:26:56.220 --> 00:26:57.890
对不起 叔叔
Sorry, Uncle.


322
00:27:05.230 --> 00:27:07.460
你是谁？ 你为什么盯着我看？
Who are you? Why were you staring at me?


323
00:27:07.460 --> 00:27:08.960
- 你叫什么名字？ - 我的名字？
- What is your name? - My name?


324
00:27:08.960 --> 00:27:11.330
- 我在哪见过你的   - 不是... 我不是...
- I know you from somewhere. - No... I wasn't...


325
00:27:11.330 --> 00:27:14.430
- 不是什么？  - 你不可能认识我
- Wasn't what? - You don't know me.


326
00:27:14.440 --> 00:27:16.240
- 我认识你的  - 不可能！
- I do know you. - No!


327
00:27:16.240 --> 00:27:19.010
- 我真认识你 你是帕尔瓦娜   - 我不是
- I do know you! You're Parvana! - I'm not!


328
00:27:19.010 --> 00:27:21.410
我是什沃吉亚 记得吗？ 学校里那个？
I am Shauzia! Remember? From school?


329
00:27:22.910 --> 00:27:26.110
- 什沃吉亚？ - 我之前是留长头发的 话说那会儿你也是
- Shauzia? - I had long hair then, but so did you.


330
00:27:26.120 --> 00:27:28.320
- 德利瓦  - 别跟别人说
- Deliwar. - Don't tell anyone.


331
00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:29.850
给你帽子
Here's your cap.


332
00:27:31.120 --> 00:27:32.920
你需要一个男孩的名字
You need to get a boy's name


333
00:27:32.920 --> 00:27:35.490
这样下次别人再问你的时候 你就不会犹豫了
so you don't hesitate next time somebody asks you.


334
00:27:35.490 --> 00:27:37.360
我现在叫德利瓦
I am Deliwar now.


335
00:27:37.360 --> 00:27:38.990
名字的意思是“勇敢”
It means "brave."


336
00:27:38.990 --> 00:27:41.360
- 你在哪呢？ - 我 我得走了
- Where are you? - I-I have to run.


337
00:27:41.360 --> 00:27:43.470
能见到你真好
It was good to see you.


338
00:27:45.200 --> 00:27:47.000
德利瓦
Deliwar.


339
00:27:47.700 --> 00:27:49.670
妈妈 请坐下吧
Mama-jan, please sit down.


340
00:27:49.670 --> 00:27:54.240
- 马上要到宵禁了 如果到时候她还没有回来呢？ - 她没事的 我...
- It will be curfew soon. What if she's not back by then? - She's fine. I'm...


341
00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:55.580
谁肚子饿了？
Who's hungry?


342
00:27:55.580 --> 00:27:58.150
帕尔瓦娜
Parvana.


343
00:27:58.150 --> 00:28:00.380
感谢真主安拉 他把你给我带回来了
Praise Allah. He has returned you to me.


344
00:28:00.380 --> 00:28:03.950
妈妈 你把馕饼都挤扁了
Mama-jan, you're squashing the naan.


345
00:28:03.950 --> 00:28:06.020
闻起来太香了 帕尔瓦娜
It smells delicious, Parvana.


346
00:28:13.330 --> 00:28:15.030
扎西
Zaki.


347
00:28:19.440 --> 00:28:21.370
是我啊 认出来了么？
It's me. See?


348
00:28:23.210 --> 00:28:26.040
我特别为你买的
I bought them especially for you.


349
00:28:29.040 --> 00:28:32.010
帕尔瓦娜？
Parvana?


350
00:28:32.010 --> 00:28:34.110
如果你现在就跑出去打水
If you run out and get some water,


351
00:28:34.120 --> 00:28:36.320
等你回来时 他就会习惯你的新样子了
he'll get used to you by the time you come back.


352
00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:38.480
- 但是我已经累了 - 快点 帕尔瓦娜
- But I'm tired. - Hurry on, Parvana.


353
00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:40.190
马上就要宵禁了
It's almost curfew.


354
00:29:08.050 --> 00:29:10.290
你看着太像他了
You look so much like him.


355
00:29:11.150 --> 00:29:12.690
去把苏莱曼的衣服换下来吧
Go change Sulayman's clothes,


356
00:29:12.690 --> 00:29:14.490
要不该弄脏了
or you'll get them dirty.


357
00:29:14.490 --> 00:29:16.290
已经脏了
They are already dirty.


358
00:29:24.200 --> 00:29:26.470
大象
Elephant.


359
00:29:26.470 --> 00:29:28.340
什么？
What?


360
00:29:28.340 --> 00:29:31.640
他想让你继续讲大象的故事
He wants you to continue your story about the elephant.


361
00:29:31.640 --> 00:29:33.640
大象
Elephant.


362
00:29:33.640 --> 00:29:35.380
好吧 嗯...
Well, um...


363
00:29:36.380 --> 00:29:37.610
在村子里
in the village,


364
00:29:37.610 --> 00:29:40.050
在兴都库什山脉脚下
under the Hindu Kush mountains,


365
00:29:40.050 --> 00:29:42.590
可怜的村民们都失声痛哭
the poor villagers cried bitter tears.


366
00:29:44.950 --> 00:29:49.390
没有了珍贵的种子 他们变得惊慌失措
They did not know what they would do without their precious bag of seeds.


367
00:29:49.390 --> 00:29:52.160
明年春天没有了种子可以去播种
They would have nothing to sow come next spring


368
00:29:52.160 --> 00:29:54.430
到了冬天也没有可以吃的食物
and nothing to eat come next winter.


369
00:29:54.430 --> 00:29:58.260
但是那个男孩 他并没有哭
But the boy, he did not cry bitter tears.


370
00:29:58.270 --> 00:30:00.470
他看向山峦 然后大喊...
He looked toward the mountain and he shouted...


371
00:30:00.470 --> 00:30:02.740
我才不害怕你呢
I am not afraid of you,


372
00:30:02.740 --> 00:30:06.440
又大又扎人的坏象王！
big, spiky, bad Elephant King!


373
00:30:12.480 --> 00:30:16.180
也许有一点点害怕
Well, maybe he was a little bit afraid.


374
00:30:16.190 --> 00:30:19.750
他告诉村里这些以苦泪洗面的人
He told the villagers who had been weeping bitter tears


375
00:30:19.750 --> 00:30:23.290
在春天之前 他就能把种子拿回来
that he would get the bag of seed back before spring.


376
00:30:23.290 --> 00:30:26.160
在春天到来之前 我就能把种子拿回来
I will get the bag of seed back before spring.


377
00:30:26.160 --> 00:30:28.660
但是他们都嘲笑了他
But they laughed.


378
00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:32.800
他们大笑不止 因他只是个孩子 并不是一位伟大的勇士
They laughed and laughed, because he was a child and not a great warrior.


379
00:30:32.800 --> 00:30:35.570
但是男孩又一次发了誓
Yet the boy repeated his promise.


380
00:30:35.570 --> 00:30:39.570
我说了 我会在春天之前把那一袋种子拿回来
I said, I will get the bag of seed back before spring.


381
00:30:39.570 --> 00:30:41.340
接着他离开了村庄
And he left the village


382
00:30:41.340 --> 00:30:43.710
向着象王的怒吼勇敢前进
to the sound of the Elephant King's roars ahead of him.


383
00:30:45.650 --> 00:30:47.520
吼！
Roar!


384
00:31:17.680 --> 00:31:20.210
妈妈 既然现在我扮成男孩了
Mama-jan, now that I am a boy


385
00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:23.220
我们就可以去监狱找爸爸了
we can go to the prison and find Baba.


386
00:31:23.220 --> 00:31:25.750
不 帕尔瓦娜 我们不能这么做
No, Parvana, we can't do that.


387
00:31:25.750 --> 00:31:27.250
- 为什么不行？ - 嘘 安静
- Why not? - Shh.


388
00:31:27.260 --> 00:31:29.720
没你想得那么简单 帕尔瓦娜
It's not that simple, Parvana.


389
00:31:29.720 --> 00:31:31.590
但我们总得试一试啊
But we have to try.


390
00:31:31.590 --> 00:31:34.190
- 我们什么也做不了  - 才不是
- There's nothing we can do. - That's not true.


391
00:31:34.200 --> 00:31:36.670
别说了 帕尔瓦娜 别惹她伤心了
Stop it, Parvana. You're upsetting her.


392
00:31:46.880 --> 00:31:49.710
嘿 嘿 我叫你站住 你怎么还跑？
Hey! Hey! I told you to stop! Why do you keep running?


393
00:31:49.710 --> 00:31:51.780
别人叫你站住的时候 你就应该乖乖听话
You should have stopped when you were told to.


394
00:31:51.780 --> 00:31:55.380
你的布卡袍呢 你为什么如此打扮就出门
Where's your burqa? Why are you dressed like this outside your house?


395
00:31:55.380 --> 00:31:58.890
我丈夫把我的布卡袍拿走了 我得去买药
My husband took my burqa. I needed to buy medicine.


396
00:31:58.890 --> 00:32:00.650
住嘴
Stop it. Stop it.


397
00:32:00.660 --> 00:32:03.760
他居然允许你出门不穿布卡袍 他该受到惩罚
He should be punished for letting you outside like this!


398
00:32:03.760 --> 00:32:06.460
- 拜托 别这样 - 你必须得替他受罚
- Please, please! Please! - You have to take his punishment!


399
00:32:10.730 --> 00:32:13.400
乖乖待在里面吧 那才是属于你的地方
Stay inside where you belong!


400
00:32:30.920 --> 00:32:33.660
德利瓦 德利瓦
Deliwar. Deliwar!


401
00:32:35.960 --> 00:32:37.990
你想好叫什么了吗？
Well? Have you remembered your name yet?


402
00:32:37.990 --> 00:32:40.790
我想我没法继续扮男孩了
I don't think I can go on like this.


403
00:32:40.800 --> 00:32:42.730
太可惜了 我还指望你帮帮我呢
Too bad. I could use some help.


404
00:32:47.770 --> 00:32:50.840
- 我看到了些事 - 你指望我能说什么？
- I saw something. - What do you want me to say?


405
00:32:50.840 --> 00:32:52.340
我本该帮忙的
I should have helped.


406
00:32:52.340 --> 00:32:55.880
- 你能做的也就是给自己招来几次鞭打了 - 但我不是男孩
- You'd have helped yourself to a good whipping, that's all. - But I'm not a boy.


407
00:32:55.880 --> 00:32:57.810
你不是男孩 也不是女孩
You're not a boy, you're not a girl.


408
00:32:57.810 --> 00:33:01.620
我需要帮助 托盘太重了 你能帮我下吗？
I need a helper because this tray is too heavy. Will you help?


409
00:33:01.620 --> 00:33:05.790
快挠挠我鼻子 如果我松手皮带会断的
Scratch my nose. Quickly. If I let go of the tray, the strap will break.


410
00:33:05.790 --> 00:33:07.350
好多了
That's better.


411
00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:08.920
- 奥狄什 - 你说什么？
- Aatish. - What?


412
00:33:08.920 --> 00:33:11.690
我想好我的名字了 就叫奥狄什
I remembered my name. It's Aatish.


413
00:33:11.690 --> 00:33:14.030
- 那可算不上是个名字 - 它的意思是“火”
- That's not really a name. - It means "fire."


414
00:33:14.030 --> 00:33:17.760
我知道它的意思 不代表这词算是个名字
I know what it means, but it's still not a name.


415
00:33:17.770 --> 00:33:19.870
可它跟我挺配的
Then it suits me fine.


416
00:33:19.870 --> 00:33:21.470
那我就叫你奥狄什好了
I'll call you Aatish then.


417
00:33:22.600 --> 00:33:25.670
如果你是个男孩 你想去哪里都行
When you're a boy you can go anywhere you like,


418
00:33:25.670 --> 00:33:27.480
奥狄什汗
Aatish Khan.


419
00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:37.620
我们要去哪？
Where are we going?


420
00:33:37.620 --> 00:33:39.360
等着瞧吧
You'll see.


421
00:33:54.900 --> 00:33:56.940
如果有人看到我们怎么办？
What if someone sees us?


422
00:33:56.940 --> 00:33:59.410
我一般都假装说我在这工作
I usually just pretend I work here.


423
00:33:59.410 --> 00:34:01.640
假话说道你自己都信了 那别人也会信
If you look like you believe it, then they will too.


424
00:34:02.910 --> 00:34:04.810
看到没 我们就是清洁工
See? We're cleaners.


425
00:34:37.080 --> 00:34:39.050
你还在等什么呢？
What are you waiting for?


426
00:34:39.050 --> 00:34:41.450
我们不拿走的话 就白白便宜给老鼠了
It's either ours, or the mice eat it.


427
00:34:41.450 --> 00:34:43.850
我得想个办法去找我爸爸
I need to find a way to see my Baba.


428
00:34:43.850 --> 00:34:46.650
喜欢的话 把我爸给你都行 反正我不想要他这样的爸爸
You can have mine if you like. I don't want him.


429
00:34:46.650 --> 00:34:50.490
自从我爸入狱后 我们就再也没听到过他的消息了
My father was taken to prison and we've heard nothing of him since.


430
00:34:50.490 --> 00:34:53.060
- 他们是不会让你见他的 帕尔瓦娜 - 但是我现在是个男孩了
- They won't let you see him, Parvana. - But I'm a boy now.


431
00:34:53.060 --> 00:34:56.800
没什么区别 无论他们是继续关着你爸爸还是放了他 你都帮不上什么忙的
Doesn't make a difference. They'll keep him or let him go, but there's nothing you can do.


432
00:34:56.800 --> 00:34:59.000
这可说不准
You don't know that.


433
00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:02.470
抱歉 但事实就是这样
I'm sorry. It's just the way it is.


434
00:35:04.910 --> 00:35:09.740
也许有办法 但是得花上很多钱
There might be a way, but you'll need lots of money.


435
00:35:09.740 --> 00:35:11.680
钱能有什么用？
What for?


436
00:35:11.680 --> 00:35:14.880
靠贿赂能办成很多事 很多很多
You can get a lot done with bribes. A lot.


